name: Tike's Peak
desc: The junior set plays at this polar-themed wonderland with pint-sized waterslides and aquatic activities.

name: Advanced Training Lab
desc: Train for your next Mars mission at a high-tech play area featuring space-themed games and activities for all ages.

name: Typhoon Lagoon Surf Pool
desc: Experience the drama of 6-foot swells at North America’s largest wave pool and the water park’s signature attraction.

name: Crush 'n' Gusher
desc: Shoot the chute on this gushing coaster-like raft ride—one of the park’s signature attractions!

name: Soarin' Around the World
desc: Take flight on a breezy, airborne adventure as you hang glide above the breathtaking wonders of the world.

name: Bay Slides
desc: Twin body slides offer scaled-down thrills for tots.

name: Ski Patrol Training Camp
desc: Hone Your Skills, Own Your Thrills  Encounter tricky obstacles, waterslides and more that offer action and adventure for aspiring alpine athletes.The frosty fun includes:Thin Ice Training Course – Test your balance by walking across ice floes.Fahrenheit Drops – Drop in on the “T-Bar,” a zip line that ends with a splash in 8.5-foot-deep water (for Guests 5 feet tall and under).Frozen Pipe Springs – Thaw out on an enclosed body slide.Cool Runners – Coast on an inner tube down curved slides flanked by melting snow.Snow Falls – Make a splash on a downhill body slide.No summer camp was ever this fun!

name: Expedition Everest - Legend of the Forbidden Mountain
desc: Careen through icy Himalayan peaks on a speeding train while avoiding the clutches of the mythic Yeti.

name: American Heritage Gallery
desc: Discover an all-new exhibition celebrating American Indian art at this museum inside the American Adventure Pavilion.

name: Bruce's Shark World
desc: Get ready for fish-friendly fun at this interactive walkthrough exhibit at The Seas with Nemo & Friends Pavilion.

name: Stave Church Gallery
desc: Explore Viking Lore  View historical items—some displayed outside of Norway for the first time—to explore how the Vikings’ beliefs impacted their daily life.Uncover the stories that guided the Vikings, beginning with the creation myth that explains how the world was created from the bones of giants, held together by a gigantic tree and populated by bold gods who inspired heroic and ruthless deeds.Marvel at their heroic ancient deities, including Odin, ruler of Asgard, Thor, the mighty protector god, Loki the trickster and Freya, goddess of love.

name: Turtle Talk With Crush
desc: Gather around a window to the ocean for a conversation in real time with your favorite totally tubular sea turtle.

name: Marketplace Carousel
desc: Take a spin on this charming Venetian carousel in the heart of Disney Springs Marketplace.

name: Marketplace Train Express
desc: Take a tiny train ride along a charming choo-choo track.

name: Marketplace Fun Fountains
desc: What makes the fountain flow? How does the water know when to go? See for yourself, but be prepared to get soaking wet!

name: Kidcot Fun Stops
desc: Pick up an international memento at any or all 11 of these World Showcase stations.

name: The Seas with Nemo & Friends
desc: Go under the sea—without getting wet—on this gentle ride based on Disney and Pixar's Finding Nemo, which finds Nemo lost again.

name: Monsters Inc. Laugh Floor
desc: Participate in a hilarious, gag-tastic interactive comedy show—starring Monsters, Inc. and company!

name: House of the Whispering Willows
desc: Shanghai Surprises  Discover some of the ingenious ways Walt Disney Imagineers wove elements of Chinese culture into every aspect of the groundbreaking Resort. View drawings, photos and artwork of the cutting-edge attractions, 6 different themed lands, 2 hotels—and the shopping, dining and entertainment district known as Disneytown. See how architecture and design together seamlessly created an authentically Disney experience that remains distinctly Chinese.

name: Gran Fiesta Tour Starring The Three Caballeros
desc: Take in the sights of Mexico and the antics of 3 feathered amigos on this gentle boat ride through the Mexico Pavilion.

name: Toy Story Mania!
desc: Zip through an exhilarating 4D shootin’ game starring Toy Story characters—and blast away.

name: Project Tomorrow: Inventing the Wonders of the Future
desc: The Ideas of Tomorrow – Today!  After your journey through Spaceship Earth, explore the latest in high-tech science.Assemble a digital human body using technology developed to perform remote surgeries. Hit the road in a driving simulation game that demonstrate accident avoidance systems. Take a peek at groundbreaking medical diagnostics for your home.You can even view the video from the future you made while riding through Spaceship Earth—and email it to family and friends from a Project Tomorrow kiosk!

name: Walt Disney World Railroad - Frontierland - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: All Aboard!  Listen to the clamor of the engine, the chug of the wheels and the call of the whistle aboard the Walt Disney World Railroad.Ride 1 of 4 meticulously restored, vintage narrow-gauge steam trains—originally built between 1916 and 1928—and enjoy a relaxing 20-minute, 1.5-mile scenic round-trip tour.It’s a convenient—and nostalgic—way to get around Magic Kingdom park!!Find a Station You can board or disembark at any of 3 stations:Near the entrance to the park on Main Street, U.S.A.The Frontierland stationThe Fantasyland station

name: Walt Disney's Enchanted Tiki Room
desc: Tropical birds, Tiki gods and colorful flowers come to life in a swinging South Seas musical extravaganza.

name: The Barnstormer
desc: Take flight above Storybook Circus with Goofy in a homemade stunt airplane for a thrilling junior roller coaster ride.

name: Walt Disney World Railroad - Fantasyland - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: All Aboard!  Listen to the clamor of the engine, the chug of the wheels and the call of the whistle as you travel aboard the Walt Disney World Railroad.Take your seat on 1 of 4 meticulously restored, vintage narrow-gauge steam trains—originally built between 1916 and 1928—and enjoy a relaxing 20-minute, 1.5-mile scenic round-trip tour.It’s a convenient—and nostalgic—way to get around Magic Kingdom park!Find a Station  You can board or disembark at any of 3 stations:Near the entrance to the park on Main Street, U.S.A.The Frontierland stationThe Fantasyland stationPicture Perfect Enjoy a blast from the past by taking advantage of an enchanted photo opportunity with one of these trains at the Fantasyland station.

name: Casey Jr. Splash 'N' Soak Station
desc: Cool off at a whimsical water play area inspired by the circus train from Walt Disney’s Dumbo.

name: Cinderella Castle
desc: Inspired by the castle in the Disney film Cinderella, this enchanting edifice is the symbol of Magic Kingdom park.

name: Under the Sea ~ Journey of The Little Mermaid
desc: Board a clamshell and become part of Ariel’s world on a musical adventure awash with scenes from the animated classic.

name: Enchanted Tales with Belle - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: Relive the magic of Disney’s Beauty and the Beast by taking part in her fairytale—alongside Belle herself!

name: Seven Dwarfs Mine Train
desc: Race through the diamond mine from Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs on a swaying family coaster ride.

name: Walt Disney World Railroad - Temporarily Unavailable
A Pirate's Adventure ~ Treasures of the Seven Seas
desc: Ahoy, mateys! Join an interactive hunt for secret treasures hidden throughout Adventureland.

name: Wilderness Explorers
desc: Follow in the footsteps of Russell from the Disney·Pixar film Up as you earn adventure badges around the park.

name: Wildlife Express Train - Rafiki's Planet Watch Station
Allergy-Friendly Trick-Or-Treat Experience – Mickey's Not-So-Scary Halloween Party
desc: Do you have a food allergy? If so, we have a special trick-or-treat experience for you!When you enter Magic Kingdom park for Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party, find a Cast Member to pick up your teal treat bag––the official color of food allergy awareness. You can also pick up teal treat bags from the official Allergy-Friendly Center in Liberty Square.Then, when you trick-or-treat with your teal bag, Cast Members will give you a special token to each treat station. And later on, you can redeem your teal tokens at our Allergy-Friendly Centers to receive your treats!Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party haunts the night on select dates from August 12 to October 31, 2022.Please note: a treat token is not needed to receive allergy-friendly candy during Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party.

name: Treat Locations for Mickey's Not-So-Scary Halloween Party
desc: Join fellow trick-or-treaters to collect scrumptious candies and treats throughout Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party! Simply follow the trick-or-treat map to track down all the magical locations and fill your bag with Halloween goodies.If you have a food allergy, please see a Cast Member to pick up a teal-colored treat bag. When you trick-or-treat with your teal bag, you’ll receive a teal token at our treat stations. Later on, you can redeem these teal tokens at our Allergy-Friendly Center in Liberty Square for your special treats!Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party haunts the night on select dates from August 12 through October 31, 2022.

name: EPCOT International Flower & Garden Festival - Topiaries
desc: Stroll through breathtaking gardens and admire topiary sculptures of cherished Disney characters at the EPCOT International Flower & Garden Festival––check back later for updates!

name: African Elephants - Disney Animals
desc: Behold the majestic elephant—the planet’s largest terrestrial animal.

name: Rhinos - Disney Animals
desc: Brace yourself for the sight of this hefty heavy-horned mammal—the world’s second largest land animal.

name: African Lions - Disney Animals
desc: Meet the real lion king—and queens—in the expansive wilds of a Disney African savanna.

name: Gorillas - Disney Animals
desc: Come salute our resident troop (family) of gorillas, the world’s largest primates.

name: Cotton-Top Tamarins - Disney Animals
desc: Fall in love with this little leaping South American monkey—and marvel at its wild hairdo.

name: Coral Reefs - Disney Animals
desc: Discover the colorful undersea world of coral reefs, which cover less than 1% of the ocean floor but are home to 25% of all ocean species.

name: Sharks and Rays - Disney Animals
desc: See jaw-dropping denizens of the deep patrolling the waters of EPCOT—then take the plunge and swim alongside them!

name: Sea Turtles - Disney Animals
desc: Watch these graceful, gliding marine animals as they totally “Crush” it in their aquarium at EPCOT.

name: Butterflies - Disney Animals
desc: Discover an abundance of native butterflies fluttering through our gardens all year round.

name: Migratory Birds - Disney Animals
desc: Wing your way over to discover a variety of fabulous feathered friends—from storks to hummingbirds.

name: Tigers - Disney Animals
desc: Marvel at the grace and beauty of the rare Sumatran tiger—one of the Earth’s most powerful predators.

name: White Rhinos - Disney Animals
desc: Brace yourself for the two-horned armored carrier known as the white rhino—the second largest land animal on Earth.

name: Black Rhinos - Disney Animals
desc: Imagine a one-ton armored tank galloping 30 mph—then stopping to grab a leafy branch with its hooked lip—the black rhino!

name: Migratory Birds at Maharajah Jungle Trek - Disney Animals
desc: Meet the highest flying bird on earth—the bar-headed goose, which crosses the Himalayas at a cruising altitude 30,000 feet!

name: Migratory Birds at The Oasis Exhibits - Disney Animals
desc: Marvel at the majestic flyways of the northern pintail duck, dubbed the ‘greyhound of the air’ for its sleek, swift elegance.

name: Migratory Birds at Tree of Life - Disney Animals
desc: Admire the long-distance flyer who delivers miles not babies—over 20,000 per year, from northern Europe to southern Africa!

name: Disney Animals
desc: Null

name: Star Wars: Rebels - The Ultimate Guide
Star Wars Launch Bay
desc: Celebrate all things Star Wars and come face-to-face with Characters from the legendary space saga.

name: Star Wars at Walt Disney World Resort
desc: Your Star Wars Adventure Awaits

name: Disney and Pixar Short Film Festival
desc: Experience popular Disney and Pixar short films—in amazing 4D.

name: Star Wars Photo Opportunities
desc: Snap a photo in a classic Star Wars setting or pose with movie props straight from a galaxy far, far away.

name: Star Wars Launch Bay Theater - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: Meet the new generation of filmmakers crafting the future of Star Wars in a short behind-the-scenes documentary.

name: Frozen Ever After
desc: Voyage to Arendelle aboard an ancient Nordic vessel as you take a musical tour of the wintery world of Frozen.

name: Disney's Animal Kingdom Theme Park at Night
Frozen at Walt Disney World Resort
Pirates at Walt Disney World Resort
desc: Null

name: Giraffes - Disney Animals
desc: Gain a new perspective on the African herbivore that stands head and shoulders above the rest.

name: Hippopotamuses - Disney Animals
desc: Discover the power and surprising grace of the mighty, water-loving hippopotamus.

name: Okapis - Disney Animals
desc: Encounter a rarely seen rainforest wonder with stripes like a zebra, the body of a horse and a head like a giraffe.

name: Miss Adventure Falls
desc: Gather your crew and climb aboard for a thrilling, whitewater voyage aboard a 4-person raft.

name: Na'vi River Journey
desc: Take a mystical journey by boat deep into Pandora’s glowing bioluminescent rainforest.

name: Avatar Flight of Passage
desc: Climb atop a winged mountain banshee for a breathtaking 3D flight over Pandora’s otherworldly landscape.

name: Reef Fish - Disney Animals
desc: Discover a dazzling variety of fish that “just keep swimming” amid our colorful coral reefs.

name: Vultures - Disney Animals
desc: Swoop in to view these formidable and fascinating birds who serve as nature’s clean-up crew.

name: Zebras at Kilimanjaro Safaris - Disney Animals
desc: It’s time to earn your stripes! Enter the world of one of the savanna’s most dazzling and iconic creatures.

name: Zebras at Gorilla Falls Exploration Trail - Disney Animals
desc: It’s time to earn your stripes! Enter the world of one of the savanna’s most dazzling and iconic creatures.

name: Invertebrates at Rafiki's Planet Watch - Disney Animals
desc: Get to know the largest group of species on our planet, invertebrates—animals without a backbone!

name: Invertebrates at Gorilla Falls Exploration Trail - Disney Animals
desc: Get to know the largest group of species on our planet, invertebrates—animals without a backbone!

name: Invertebrates at EPCOT - Disney Animals
desc: Get to know the largest group of species on our planet, invertebrates—animals without a backbone!

name: Invertebrates - Disney Animals
desc: They may be spineless, but invertebrates are the backbone of a healthy ecosystem.

name: Zebras - Disney Animals
desc: Earn your stripes and get to know one of the savanna’s most iconic ungulates from A to Z.

name: Horses - Disney Animals
desc: Get to know the magnificent equines who live and work at Walt Disney World Resort.

name: Pandora – The World of Avatar
desc: Journey to an inspiring land that celebrates the magic of nature. Located in Disney’s Animal Kingdom park, Pandora lets eco-tourists join Alpha Centauri Expeditions (ACE) for the adventure of a lifetime—to encounter floating mountains, tour a bioluminescent forest and ride winged banshees.In partnership with ACE, visitors of all ages will discover the culture of the Valley of Mo’ara and celebrate the striking beauty and incredible power of this natural world.Featuring never-before-seen wonders, unique dining experiences and more, welcome to a place similar to Earth… but different in so many ways—Pandora, only at Walt Disney World Resort.

name: Flamingos - Disney Animals
desc: Pretty in pink, the fabulous flamingo is a fascinating feathered creature.

name: Gibbons - Disney Animals
desc: Go ape over gibbons—the agile acrobats of the rainforest.

name: African Birds - Disney Animals
desc: Encounter the wonder, colors and sounds of magnificent birds from Africa.

name: Vintage Amphicar Tours
desc: Cruise Lake Buena Vista on a leisurely tour aboard a vintage amphibious car.

name: Aerophile – The World Leader in Balloon Flight
desc: Float high above it all in the world’s largest hand-painted helium balloon.

name: Walt Disney Presents
desc: Explore Walt Disney’s legendary legacy through a fascinating multimedia journey that includes rare artifacts.

name: Slinky Dog Dash
desc: Take off on a family-friendly coaster that twists and turns past giant toys and springs across Andy’s oversized backyard!

name: Alien Swirling Saucers
desc: Take an intergalactic spin with the adorable aliens from Toy Story.

name: Toy Story Land
desc: Prepare to play big and have more fun than humanly possible at Walt Disney World Resort!Imagine your family and friends shrinking down to the size of a toy alongside Woody, Buzz Lightyear, Jessie and the rest of your Toy Story pals—all in the so-much-larger-than-life setting of Andy’s backyard.It’s gonna to be the rootin’-est, tootin’-est time ever, one you’re invited to discover in an all-new land at Disney’s Hollywood Studios!This is your chance to be surrounded by giant building blocks and board games that Andy’s rigged up into a playground straight out of his vivid imagination—where kids and grown-ups alike can play with new attractions, fan-favorite experiences and other Toy Story adventures.So buckle up your space ranger utility belt, set your lasers for big fun with some of your best pals… and get ready for the biggest play date of all time.Download the Play Disney Parks App Before You Visit Explore the theme parks in a whole new way with Play Disney Parks, a mobile app that turns wait time into play time and connects family & friends to the parks like never before—with games that interact with select attraction queues, unique experiences that bring surrounding environments to life, Disney trivia, achievements, music and more!

name: Coca-Cola Polar Bear Photo Op Experience - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: Share a hug and a photo op with the iconic Coca-Cola Polar Bear.

name: Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge
desc: For the first time ever, there’s a place where you can live your adventure in a galaxy far, far away!Learn what to know before you visit the Walt Disney World theme parks.

name: Play Disney Parks
desc: Disney Princess ChallengeMake our royal trivia test the crowning achievement of your week! Play Now!Interactive Fun Celebrate the stories of the Parks with games and experiences like Slinky Dog Dash, Splash Mountain, Star Wars: Galaxy’s Edge, and more! Disney Trivia Put your knowledge to the test with Disney trivia and join in the fun, anytime, anywhere! Achievements Collect and share uniquely themed achievements as you play. Each one is a digital collectible all its own—earned for playing games, answering trivia and more.  The more you explore with Play Disney Parks, the more there is to discover! Download the app today through the App Store and on Google Play. Message, data and roaming rates may apply. name: Mickey & Minnie's Runaway Railway
desc: Zip away on a zany adventure through a cartoon universe crammed with surprises.

name: Millennium Falcon: Smugglers Run
desc: Fly the Millennium Falcon on a thrilling interactive smuggling mission.

name: Star Wars: Rise of the Resistance
desc: Join the Resistance in an unforgettable battle against the First Order on this exciting ride.

name: Star Wars: Datapad on Play Disney Parks Mobile App
desc: Explore Star Wars: Galaxy’s Edge with the Star Wars: Datapad to enhance your adventure!

name: Lightning McQueen's Racing Academy
desc: Get pumped for a high-octane, first-of-its-kind show that’ll put you in the middle of the Disney and Pixar Cars universe.

name: The Animation Experience at Conservation Station
desc: Discover the influence of real life animals as you create your own sketch of a beloved Disney character.

name: Asian Small-Clawed Otters - Disney Animals
desc: Discover Asian small-clawed otters—and learn what makes these playful creatures otter-ly amazing!

name: Komodo Dragons - Disney Animals
desc: Get to know the Komodo dragon—a not-so-mythical creature that’s just as fascinating as its fairytale counterpart.

name: African Hogs - Disney Animals
desc: Go absolutely hog wild over these playful African pigs that you can’t help but love—tusks, warts and all!

name: Ankole Cattle - Disney Animals
desc: Discover this ancient African cattle breed featuring massive horns.

name: Meerkats - Disney Animals
desc: Dig into the bustling world of one of Africa’s most industrious underground architects!

name: Manatees - Disney Animals
desc: “No wake zone” ahead! Slow down to take in the grace of these large water-dwelling mammals.

name: Beauty and the Beast Sing-Along
desc: Settle in at a cozy French cinema for a 15-minute film featuring songs from the animated classic, Beauty and the Beast.

name: Awesome Planet
desc: Discover the Wonder  Experience a call to action to protect the Earth. In a partnership with the Disney Conservation Fund, this all-new film uses in-theater effects (including wind, scents and water) to tell the story of life on our planet and why it’s vitally important to care for it.

name: Remy's Ratatouille Adventure - New!
desc: Feel like you’ve shrunk down to Chef Remy’s size for a 4D culinary adventure based on the Disney and Pixar film Ratatouille. When you’re small, life is a big adventure!

name: Vacation Fun - An Original Animated Short with Mickey & Minnie
desc: Take your seat at the Mickey Shorts Theater for an original animated short starring Mickey and Minnie Mouse.

name: Palais du Cinéma
desc: Step into some of the world’s most enchanting stories. At the Palais du Cinema, you’ll explore 6 distinct gallery cases honoring the costumes, music and artwork that brought French literature to life through cinema, theater, ballet and opera. Catch a glimpse of how these stories inspired artists from around the globe, including those who created such timeless Disney classics as Sleeping Beauty, Cinderella and—of course—Beauty and the Beast.

name: Disney Park Pass
desc: When You ArriveDuring your scheduled arrival window, head to the park’s Main Entrance and use your MagicBand or card that is linked to your account.To enter one of the parks, each Guest is required to have a theme park reservation in addition to valid admission. Disney Park Pass are non-transferable, have no cash value and are void if transferred or sold. Disney Park Pass is subject to cancellation at any time. Park entry not guaranteed.Separate theme park admission required. Guests must use the same admission ticket or pass for park entry that was used to make the Disney Park Pass. Park entry is subject to capacity closures and other restrictions. This Disney Park Pass does not hold monetary value and no refunds will be issued if it is not used. A Disney Park Pass does not guarantee park entry or access to any experience, attraction, or dining location.Children under 3 years of age do not need a Disney Park Pass or park admission—they may join you when you redeem your Disney Park Pass.

name: Disney Fab 50 Character Collection - New!
desc: Across all 4 theme parks, 50 golden characters wait to be discovered during The World’s Most Magical Celebration!

name: Cinderella Castle Mural of Memories
desc: Add your Disney PhotoPass photo to an augmented reality mural superimposed on Cinderella Castle.

name: Affection Section
desc: Encounter a variety of adorable animals at the only petting zoo at the Walt Disney World Resort.

name: Astro Orbiter
desc: Lift Off!  Hold on tight as your retro 2-passenger spacecraft levitates high into the air, picks up speed and begins orbiting a galaxy of planets while the sights and sounds of Tomorrowland whirl by far below.You’re the Captain Now Control how high you fly by pulling or pushing the lever inside your ship.

name: Big Thunder Mountain Railroad
desc: Race through a haunted gold mine aboard a speeding train on this thrilling coaster-style ride.

name: Buzz Lightyear's Space Ranger Spin
desc: Fire your laser to earn points and defeat the Evil Emperor Zurg as you journey through a galactic space battle.

name: Castaway Creek
desc: Drift away on an inner tube as you float down this scenic lazy river that encircles the entire water park.

name: Chairlift
desc: Enjoy a leisurely, scenic ride to the summit of Mount Gushmore on a colorful chairlift.

name: Prince Charming Regal Carrousel
desc: Ride atop a regal steed and gallop through a whirling backdrop of wondrous color and whimsical music.

name: Conservation Station
desc: Get an in-depth look at animal habitats around the globe and see the expert veterinary care our animals receive.

name: Cross Country Creek
desc: An Arctic Adventure  Grab an inner tube and paddle gently down the stream as you glide through mysterious caves and illuminated grottoes, under bridges and past a lush green forest. Bask in the refreshing spring water that’s made its way down Mount Gushmore—and look out for bubbling geysers, waterfalls and leaky pipes along the way.Pay a quick visit to Ice Gator, who’s at home sick with a cold. Just watch out for his sneeze!Guest can pick up an inner tube at any of the 7 landings along the route.

name: DINOSAUR
desc: Travel back in time on a perilous prehistoric race to rescue a dinosaur—before the meteor strikes.

name: Dino-Sue
desc: A T-Rex Named Sue  Stand in the shadow of an incredible replica of the largest and most complete T-Rex fossil ever found. Pose for pictures with the meticulously detailed, 13-foot tall, 40-foot long prehistoric superstar. Only 67 million years young, Sue was discovered in the Black Hills of South Dakota in 1990. Named after fossil hunter Sue Hendrickson, the skeleton is one of the most famous fossil finds of the 20th century. It’s also the most complete, with over 90% of her bones found and excavated. While the real Sue is on display at The Field Museum in Chicago, Illinois, Dino-Sue makes her home here in sunny Florida.

name: Discovery Island Trails
desc: Stroll tranquil pathways around the Tree of Life and discover a lush landscape brimming with wildlife.

name: Downhill Double Dipper
desc: It’s All Downhill from Here  A retractable starting gate is all that stands between you and victory. Anticipation builds as you and your opponent wait on inner tubes at the top of twin enclosed waterslides. Suddenly, the gates retract—and you’re off!Disappear into a black hole and plummet 50 feet downhill at exhilarating speeds. Hurtle through darkness, then emerge just in time for the big splashdown.May the fastest racer come in first!

name: Dumbo the Flying Elephant
desc: Soar high in the sky—and see an elephant fly—on a whimsical flight aboard Dumbo.

name: Fossil Fun Games
desc: Play wacky carnival-style, dinosaur-themed games and have a mammoth good time!

name: Frontierland Shootin' Arcade
desc: Take aim at nearly 100 targets in an Old West-themed shooting gallery.

name: Gallery of Arts and History
desc: Discover what it takes to thrive—and compete in—the challenging environment of the Sahara.

name: Gangplank Falls
desc: Climb aboard an oversized inner tube and ride a scenic, winding course down the mountain.

name: Humunga Kowabunga
desc: Plummet down Mount Mayday for a near-vertical, 5-story drop—in the dark!

name: ImageWorks - The "What If" Labs
desc: Let your imagination run wild in a creative play space where little ones can explore their senses.

name: Impressions de France
desc: Enjoy an 18-minute film showcasing the grandeur, charm and romance of one of Europe’s most enchanting countries.

name: "it's a small world"
desc: Embark on a whimsical boat ride past a jubilant chorus of children from around the globe.

name: It's Tough to be a Bug!
desc: Discover what it’s like to be a bug during this 3D film and live show inspired by the Disney and Pixar movie A Bug’s Life.

name: Muppet*Vision 3D
desc: Experience the magic of the Muppets during a hilarious film and live-action extravaganza.

name: Journey Into Imagination With Figment
desc: Figment the playful dragon is your guide on this delightful ride through the sensory labs of Imagination Institute.

name: Jungle Cruise
desc: Chart a course for high adventure on a scenic and comedic boat tour of exotic rivers across Asia, Africa and South America.

name: Kali River Rapids
desc: Set out on a thrilling whitewater adventure through a lush jungle in the heart of Asia.

name: Keelhaul Falls
desc: Haul yourself up Mount Mayday and enjoy a swift, scenic ride down on a 1-person inner tube.

name: Ketchakiddee Creek
desc: Little squirts get to splash all day at this water wonderland designed just for them.

name: Kilimanjaro Safaris
desc: Set off in an open-air vehicle for a guided tour of an African savanna—and spot live animals roaming free.

name: Leave A Legacy
desc: Leave A Legacy  Epcot is a park that celebrates the world—a place that invites collaboration and connections, where people from all cultures can come together and share their stories. From 1999 to June 2007, Leave a Legacy offered Guests the opportunity to have their pictures taken and etched onto steel tiles, which were mounted on panels, creating a beautiful representation of our global community.Leave a Legacy continues to celebrate the spirit of optimism.When visiting Epcot, Guests can use their device to scan the QR code, located at the Leave a Legacy display outside of the main entrance touch points, to utilize the new tile finder search feature. Please follow the instructions on the printed signs – located at each end of the Leave a Legacy displays. Guests can also visit the Epcot Guest Relations team for assistance.

name: Liberty Square Riverboat
desc: Cruise the scenic Rivers of America aboard an authentic steam-powered paddle wheeler.

name: Living with the Land
desc: Cruise past greenhouses on a gentle boat tour and discover the surprising history of farming.

name: Mad Tea Party
desc: Spin ‘round and ‘round in a giant teacup during a madcap music-filled whirlwind.

name: Maharajah Jungle Trek
desc: Traipse down mystical trails to discover a wonderland of tigers and other wild animals.

name: Main Street Vehicles
desc: Travel back in time during a breezy drive down Main Street, U.S.A. in a charming turn-of-the-century vehicle.

name: Mayday Falls
desc: Brave the rapids—and the bumps—on the highest and longest waterslide at Disney’s Typhoon Lagoon.

name: Melt-Away Bay
desc: A Day at the Beach  Listen to the sound of gentle waves lapping the shore—or grab an inner tube and bob in the warm swells.Mount Gushmore’s waterfalls cascade into massive Melt-Away Bay, creating short waves perfect for leisurely floating, with just enough excitement. Swim out to the rocky outcrops and bask under a refreshing waterfall.Then, luxuriate in a lounge chair on the white-sand beaches.

name: Mickey's PhilharMagic
desc: Disney magic meets Disney music in this spectacular 12-minute, 3D fantasy adventure starring Donald Duck.

name: Mission: SPACE
desc: Blast off on a thrilling simulated NASA-style mission to Mars—or orbit the Earth on a more gentle ride through space.

name: Canada Far and Wide in Circle-Vision 360
desc: Sweeping Scenic Views  Explore Canada in a newly updated edition of the classic, 12-minute Epcot Circle-Vision 360 presentation.

name: Gorilla Falls Exploration Trail
desc: Trek through a lush tropical forest and spot gorillas, hippos, zebra and more in their natural habitats.

name: Peter Pan's Flight
desc: Embark on a high-flying adventure over iconic scenes made famous in Disney’s animated film.

name: Pirates of the Caribbean
desc: Set sail on a swashbuckling voyage to a long-forgotten time and place when pirates and privateers ruled the seas.

name: Reflections of China
desc: Journey through ancient and modern China during a spectacular 12-minute Circle-Vision 360° film.

name: Rock 'n' Roller Coaster Starring Aerosmith
desc: Race along the darkened freeways of Los Angeles in a super-stretch limo to the rockin' tunes of Aerosmith.

name: Runoff Rapids
desc: Triple Threat  Experience 3 times the thrills as you twist and turn your way 600 feet down the mountain.Each slide offers a unique experience: On the center slide, you’ll launch on a dark, fully enclosed trip to the bottom with just pinpricks of light peeking through.On the 2 outer slides, you’ll zip over, around and under the snaking coils of the center slide.All 3 high-speed slides come to the same conclusion—a major splashdown!

name: SeaBase
desc: Explore the magic and mystery of life under the sea at this ocean-themed destination, home to a fin-tastic aquarium.

name: Slush Gusher
desc: Zoom down an exhilarating 90-foot, high-speed waterslide in the shadow of Summit Plummet.

name: Snow Stormers
desc: Power Through the (Melted) Powder  Lay on a toboggan-style mat on your belly and careen down a zigzag course headfirst to the bottom of Mount Gushmore.Bank through twists and turns as you fly past the flag markers of the slalom gates—like in a real downhill ski race!Each of the 3 snow-capped flumes is 350 feet long, so you can race your friends to the big splashdown at the bottom.

name: Space Mountain
desc: Blast off on a rip-roaring rocket into the furthest reaches of outer space on this roller-coaster ride in the dark.

name: Spaceship Earth
desc: Travel through time and explore the remarkable history of human communication from the Stone Age to the computer age.

name: Splash Mountain
desc: Drop into a whimsical world filled with classic characters and songs on this thrilling log-flume adventure.

name: Star Tours – The Adventures Continue
desc: Make the jump to hyperspace on a thrilling 3D space flight to legendary destinations from the Star Wars saga.

name: Storm Slides
desc: Take the Water by Storm  Choose from one of 3 bodacious body slides: Jib Jammer, Stern Burner or Rudder Buster.No matter which you pick, you’re in for an aquatic adventure as you zip, twist and turn your way past rocky outcrops and lush greenery, through grottoes and down into an epic 3-story-high waterfall finale.

name: Summit Plummet
desc: One Fearsome Freefall  Plunge 12 stories almost straight down, rocketing through a darkened tunnel and into a massive spray of whitewater after a 360-foot-long, high-speed descent.Hardcore thrill-seekers won’t want to miss this slide so steep, you can’t see where you’re going—until you’re there!Do you dare experience the most extreme attraction at Disney’s Blizzard Beach water park?

name: Swiss Family Treehouse
desc: Explore the ultimate treehouse—and behold breathtaking views—inspired by the classic Disney film, Swiss Family Robinson.

name: Teamboat Springs
desc: Fun is a family affair on one of the world’s longest group whitewater raft adventures, for up to 6 riders.

name: Test Track
desc: Design a virtual concept car and put it to the test on this thrilling, high-octane attraction.

name: The American Adventure
desc: Feel the spirit that propelled America to greatness in an inspiring retelling of our nation’s history.

name: The Boneyard
desc: Fun with Fossils  A world of prehistoric marvels awaits! Kids ages 10 and under are invited to clamber across rope bridges, climb through mysterious caves and hurl down twisting slides.At the dig site, help excavate fossils from a Triceratops and a Tyrannosaurus Rex. Discover lots more dino-sized surprises as you have a blast digging up the past.Parents of busy explorers can enjoy a shaded seating area at the dig site, where large fans help cool things down.

name: Haunted Mansion
desc: Climb aboard a gloomy Doom Buggy for a grave journey through a labyrinth of haunted chambers.

name: The Magic Carpets of Aladdin
desc: Fly high over Adventureland on an enchanted carpet ride inspired by the Disney movie Aladdin.

name: The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh
desc: Travel through Hundred-Acre Wood in an oversized Hunny Pot and get lost in the pages of A.A. Milne’s classic tales.

name: The Oasis Exhibits
desc: Roam a lush, tropical paradise that’s home to exotic animals.

name: Tree of Life
desc: Celebrate all living creatures at the iconic symbol of Disney’s Animal Kingdom park.

name: The Twilight Zone Tower of Terror™
desc: Hurtle up and down aboard a haunted elevator-style lift. You’re about to enter… The Twilight Zone!

name: Toboggan Racers
desc: Ready, Set, Snow!  Grab your mat, take your mark and zip headfirst on your belly to the bottom of Mount Gushmore on a 250-foot-long “toboggan” race that features 3 exhilarating dips and hills.Feel the rush as you crest each rise. May the best mat win!

name: Tom Sawyer Island
desc: Travel by log raft to this secret rustic hideaway inspired by the stories of Mark Twain.

name: Tomorrowland Speedway
desc: Put the pedal to the metal in your very own hotrod and cruise along a scenic miniature motorway.

name: Tomorrowland Transit Authority PeopleMover
desc: Embark on a 10-minute tour of Tomorrowland aboard this mass transit system of the future.

name: TriceraTop Spin
desc: Fly high on a dinosaur around a twirling tin-toy top at this delightful carnival-inspired attraction.

name: Walt Disney World Railroad - Main Street, U.S.A. - Temporarily Unavailable
desc: Celebrate classic Americana at this picturesque train station near the entrance to Magic Kingdom park.

name: Walt Disney's Carousel of Progress
desc: Travel through the 20th century and marvel at the evolution of technology during this classic Audio-Animatronics show.

name: Wildlife Express Train
desc: Cross the African savanna on a rustic locomotive for a behind-the-scenes look at the park’s animals.

name: Mexico Folk Art Gallery
desc: Bringing Day of the Dead to Life  You’re invited to “Remember Me!” – La Celebración del Día de Muertos, an exhibit that captures the beauty and spirit of the Day of the Dead holiday. One of the most important events on the country’s calendar, the celebration honors the dearly departed with parades, elaborate costumes and vibrant arts and crafts.Tour the gallery’s intricately cut pieces of papel picado as well as calaveras, or decorative skulls made of sugar. See pre-Hispanic art that hints at the day’s beginnings and contemporary pieces that highlight its influence in modern Mexican life.Don’t miss the iconic sculpture Bridal Couple, who did not let death part them.

name: Bijutsu-kan Gallery
desc: Adorable Art on Display  The current Bijutsu-kan Gallery show, “Kawaii: Japan’s Cute Culture,” takes a look at this pop-culture phenomenon that’s swept the globe. Kawaii means cute or loveable—and represents an obsession with all things darling, like Hello Kitty, which is included in the exhibit. You’ll discover how kawaii is rooted deep in Japan’s Shinto past and how it’s become a core aspect of Japanese culture—and a new form of self-expression.Tour a replica Tokyo apartment of a kawaii superfan bursting with all things precious—and prepare for major cuteness overload. Hello Kitty is the copyright of SANRIO® CO., LTD.

name: Country Bear Jamboree
desc: Have a knee-slappin’ good time at this jolly country-and-western musical revue starring a cast of singing bears.

name: The Hall of Presidents
desc: Behold all 45 Presidents of the United States in a stirring show tracing the nation’s history.

name: Guardians of the Galaxy: Cosmic Rewind - New!
desc: Take off on an intergalactic chase through space and time with the Guardians of the Galaxy.

name: Coral Reef Restaurant Spotting Guide
desc: Discover a few fun facts about some of the amazing animals you’ll see while dining at Coral Reef Restaurant.

name: Enhanced Nighttime Spectaculars
desc: Don’t just watch the show—be a part of it! MagicBand+ has created a mesmerizing new way for you to celebrate at the end of each day!With your MagicBand+, you will now be able to enjoy nighttime spectaculars in an even more immersive and captivating way! Your MagicBand+ will light up, vibrate and interact with certain shows and spectaculars, creating a truly connected experience.You can even choose your own custom color and light settings so you light up the night in style!

name: Star Wars: Batuu Bounty Hunters
desc: Star Wars: Batuu Bounty Hunters is an exciting new quest that allows you to become a bounty hunter in a galaxy far, far away!With the power of MagicBand+ and the Disney Play app, you’ll be able to find virtual bounties throughout Black Spire Outpost in Star Wars: Galaxy’s Edge.First, you’ll be assigned a bounty at a job board in Star Wars: Galaxy’s Edge. Next, you’ll search for this bounty guided by your MagicBand+’s colorful lighting animations and haptic vibrations. Finally, unlock hidden surprises from the Star Wars galaxy in a unique, interactive way!Play now!

name: Disney Fab 50 Quest
desc: With the power of MagicBand+, the Disney Fab 50 Quest allows you to help Tinker Bell spread pixie dust across all 4 parks with the Disney Play app!Using your MagicBand+, locate the 36 golden sculptures featuring one or 2 of your favorite Disney characters across Magic Kingdom park, EPCOT, Disney’s Hollywood Studios and Disney’s Animal Kingdom theme park.When you collect all 50 characters, you’ll be able to unlock doorways into augmented reality worlds of enchanting magic featuring some of your favorite Disney characters!Play now!

name: Disney Springs Art Walk: A Canvas of Expression
